args: All right, Notte. It's time to make the cake\nthat {player_name}'s mother\nused to make.
Lemme at those eggs! And you better\nwatch out, cream, 'cause I'm comin'\nfor you next!
I'm not completely certain what the cake\nis meant to taste like, so let's start by\naiming for a clean, classic flavor.
I'll have you taste-test the first one,\nthen we'll make adjustments as we go.
And so, Cleo and Notte worked together to\nproduce a traditional Alberian cake.
...And there we are. Would you please\ntake a bite and see what you think, Notte?
Ohmigosh, this is AMAAAAZING!\nWhen I die, promise that you'll stuff\nthis cake into my coffin.
I'm glad to hear it. ...Well, perhaps not\nthe coffin part.
Still, how does it compare to the cake\n{player_name}'s mother made?
It's close—like, REAL close—but it's not\ntotally there yet.
I feel like her cake was a little...fluffier.\nOh, and the cream was sweeter.
Understood. I'll make some slight\nadjustments on the next one.
Over and over, Cleo attempted her cake,\nmaking adjustments to each subsequent bake.
...And we're done. Now then, Notte?\nAnother taste test, if you would?
Just hang on for a little bit longer.\nThe cake isn't quite perfect yet.
Oh man, this is pure agony, buuut...\n*nibble*
Nnngh... Something's different...\nDon't know what... Too full...
If all the adjustments I've made this far\nstill aren't getting it right, perhaps there's\nsomething wrong with my baking method.
Well, we won't get anywhere if we just\nstand here with furrowed brows.
Hey there, Cleo. Do you need something?
Tell me about your mother's cake again.
I've tried countless times to replicate it,\nbut I can't seem to get it right.
Really? I'm surprised. It's a pretty simple\ncake, all in all.
Was there anything else you remember\nabout it?
Any detail, no matter how minute,\nwould be useful.
Well, I remember how it used to have\nthe aroma of fresh strawberries.
You mean in addition to the ones she put\non top of it?
Yeah. It was more like the whole cake\nsmelled like them.
I always wondered why that was.
Uh, yeah, what she said!\nTotally eureka!
I'm not certain this will work, but there's\nsomething I'd like to try.
Having gleaned a clue from the prince,\nCleo set out to make the cake anew.
It looks amazing—but also not really any\ndifferent from all the other ones.
I know it looks the same, but the\ningredients are slightly altered.
Now then, please take a sample.
Well, guess it's been an hour or so since\nI last ate cake, sooo... *chomp*
It's a perfect match! You NAILED it!
What the heck did you do?
I mixed a bit of this strawberry sauce\ninto the batter.
*sniff* Oh man, I can actually smell it\nin there!
I believe this is how his mother managed\nto give the cake its distinctive aroma.
It's a rather clever idea, given his\nstated fondness for strawberries.
Aw! It's like the cake had his mom's love\nbaked right inside!
So that means we're finished, right?
Now we just gotta grab a plate and feed it\nto {player_name}!
Let us bring it to him at once.
